{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm going to try to give you a view of the world as I see it,"},{"time":6000,"text":"the problems and the opportunities that we face,"},{"time":10000,"text":"and then ask the question if we should be optimistic or pessimistic."},{"time":14000,"text":"And then I'll let you in on a secret, which is why I am an incurable optimist."},{"time":20000,"text":"Let me start off showing you an Al Gore movie that you may have seen before."},{"time":26000,"text":"Now, you've all seen \"Inconvenient Truth.\" This is a little more inconvenient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35000,"text":"(Video): Man: ... extremely dangerous questions."},{"time":37000,"text":"Because, with our present knowledge, we have no idea what would happen."},{"time":41000,"text":"Even now, man may be unwittingly changing the world's climate"},{"time":45000,"text":"through the waste products of his civilization."},{"time":48000,"text":"Due to our release, through factories and automobiles every year,"},{"time":51000,"text":"of more than six billion tons of carbon dioxide --"},{"time":54000,"text":"which helps air absorb heat from the sun --"},{"time":57000,"text":"our atmosphere seems to be getting warmer."},{"time":60000,"text":"This is bad?"},{"time":62000,"text":"Well, it's been calculated a few degrees' rise in the earth's temperature would"},{"time":66000,"text":"melt the polar ice caps."},{"time":76000,"text":"And if this happens, an inland sea would fill a good portion of the Mississippi Valley."},{"time":81000,"text":"Tourists in glass-bottomed boats would be viewing the drowned towers of Miami"},{"time":85000,"text":"through 150 feet of tropical water."},{"time":89000,"text":"For, in weather, we're not only dealing with forces of a far greater variety"},{"time":94000,"text":"than even the atomic physicist encounters, but with life itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98000,"text":"Larry Brilliant: Should we feel good, or should we feel bad"},{"time":102000,"text":"that 50 years of foreknowledge accomplished so little?"},{"time":108000,"text":"Well, it depends, really, on what your goals are."},{"time":111000,"text":"And I think, as my goals, I always go back to Gandhi's talisman."},{"time":118000,"text":"When Mahatma Gandhi was asked,"},{"time":120000,"text":"\"How do you know if the next act that you are about to do is the right one"},{"time":126000,"text":"or the wrong one?\" he said, \"Consider the face of the poorest,"},{"time":132000,"text":"most vulnerable human being that you ever chanced upon,"},{"time":138000,"text":"and ask yourself if the act that you contemplate will be of benefit to that person."},{"time":144000,"text":"And if it will be, it's the right thing to do, and if not, rethink it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":150000,"text":"For those of us in this room, it's not just the poorest and the most vulnerable individual,"},{"time":155000,"text":"it's the community, it's the culture, it's the world itself."},{"time":160000,"text":"And the trends for those who are at the periphery of our society,"},{"time":165000,"text":"who are the poorest and the most vulnerable,"},{"time":168000,"text":"the trends give rise to a great case for pessimism."},{"time":174000,"text":"But there's also a wonderful case for optimism."},{"time":177000,"text":"Let's review them both. First of all, the megatrends."},{"time":183000,"text":"There's two degrees, or three degrees of climate change baked into the system."},{"time":190000,"text":"It will cause rising seas. It will cause saline deposited into wells and into lands."},{"time":198000,"text":"It will disproportionately harm the poorest and the most vulnerable,"},{"time":202000,"text":"as will the increasing rise of population."},{"time":207000,"text":"Even though we've dodged Paul Ehrlich's population bomb,"},{"time":210000,"text":"and we will not see 20 billion people in this decade, as he had forecast,"},{"time":216000,"text":"we eat as if we were 20 billion."},{"time":219000,"text":"And we consume so much that again, a rise of 6.5 billion to 9.5 billion"},{"time":228000,"text":"in our grandchildren's lifetime will disproportionately hurt"},{"time":232000,"text":"the poorest and the most vulnerable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236000,"text":"That's why they migrate to cities."},{"time":240000,"text":"That's why in June of this year, we passed, as a species, 51 percent of us living in cities,"},{"time":246000,"text":"and bustees, and slums, and shantytowns."},{"time":251000,"text":"The rural areas are no longer producing as much food as they did."},{"time":255000,"text":"The green revolution never reached Africa."},{"time":258000,"text":"And with desertification, sandstorms, the Gobi Desert, the Ogaden,"},{"time":265000,"text":"we are finding increasing difficulty of a hectare"},{"time":269000,"text":"to produce as many calories as it did even 15 years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274000,"text":"So humans are turning more towards animal consumption."},{"time":279000,"text":"In Africa last year, Africans ate 600 million wild animals,"},{"time":284000,"text":"and consumed two billion kilograms of bush meat."},{"time":289000,"text":"And every kilogram of bush meat contained hundreds of thousands of novel viruses"},{"time":295000,"text":"that have never been charted, the genomic sequences of which we don't know."},{"time":301000,"text":"Their fitness for creating pandemics we are unaware of,"},{"time":306000,"text":"but we are ripe for zoonotic-borne, emerging communicable diseases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314000,"text":"Increasingly, I would say explosive growth of technology."},{"time":318000,"text":"Most of us are the beneficiaries of that growth. But it has a dark side"},{"time":325000,"text":"-- in bioweapons, and in technology that puts us on a collision course"},{"time":330000,"text":"to magnify any anger, hatred or feeling of marginalization."},{"time":338000,"text":"And in fact, with increasing globalization --"},{"time":342000,"text":"for which there are big winners and even bigger losers"},{"time":346000,"text":"-- today the world is more diverse and unfair than perhaps it has ever been in history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354000,"text":"One percent of us own 40 percent of all the goods and services."},{"time":361000,"text":"What will happen if the billion people today who live on less than one dollar a day"},{"time":368000,"text":"rise to three billion in the next 30 years?"},{"time":373000,"text":"The one percent will own even more than 40 percent of all the world's goods"},{"time":378000,"text":"and services. Not because they've grown richer,"},{"time":382000,"text":"but because the rest of the world has grown increasingly poorer."},{"time":387000,"text":"Last week, Bill Clinton at the TED Awards said,"},{"time":389000,"text":"\"This situation is unprecedented, unequal, unfair and unstable.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":396000,"text":"So there's lots of reason for pessimism."},{"time":399000,"text":"Darfur is, at its origin, a resource war."},{"time":406000,"text":"Last year, there were 85,000 riots in China,"},{"time":411000,"text":"230 a day, that required police or military intervention."},{"time":416000,"text":"Most of them were about resources."},{"time":419000,"text":"We are facing an unprecedented number, scale of disasters."},{"time":424000,"text":"Some are weather-related, human-rights related, epidemics."},{"time":429000,"text":"And the newly emerging diseases may make H5N1 and bird flu"},{"time":435000,"text":"a quaint forerunner of things to come. It's a destabilized world."},{"time":443000,"text":"And unlike destabilized world in the past, it will be broadcast to you on YouTube,"},{"time":448000,"text":"you will see it on digital television and on your cell phones."},{"time":452000,"text":"What will that lead to?"},{"time":454000,"text":"For some, it will lead to anger, religious and sectarian violence and terrorism."},{"time":461000,"text":"For others, withdrawal, nihilism, materialism."},{"time":470000,"text":"For us, where does it take us, as social activists and entrepreneurs?"},{"time":475000,"text":"As we look at these trends, do we become despondent, or will we become energized?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":484000,"text":"Let's look at one case, the case of Bangladesh."},{"time":489000,"text":"First, even if carbon dioxide emissions stopped today,"},{"time":494000,"text":"global warming would continue."},{"time":497000,"text":"And even with global warming -- if you can see these blue lines,"},{"time":501000,"text":"the dotted line shows that even if emissions of greenhouse gasses stopped today,"},{"time":510000,"text":"the next decades will see rising sea levels."},{"time":515000,"text":"A minimum of 20 to 30 inches of increase in sea levels is the best case"},{"time":522000,"text":"that we can hope for, and it could be 10 times that."},{"time":526000,"text":"What will that do to Bangladesh? Let's take a look."},{"time":529000,"text":"So here's Bangladesh."},{"time":536000,"text":"70 percent of Bangladesh is at less than five feet above sea level."},{"time":543000,"text":"Let's go up and take a look at the Himalayas."},{"time":545000,"text":"And we'll watch as global warming makes them melt. More water comes down,"},{"time":550000,"text":"the deforested areas, here in the Tarai, will be unable to absorb the effluent,"},{"time":556000,"text":"because trees are like straws that suck up the extra seasonal water."},{"time":562000,"text":"Now we're looking down south, through the Kali Gandaki."},{"time":565000,"text":"Many of you, I think, have probably trekked here."},{"time":568000,"text":"And we're going to cruise down and take a look at Bangladesh"},{"time":573000,"text":"and see what the impact will be of twin increases in water"},{"time":579000,"text":"coming from the north, and in the seas rising from the south."},{"time":585000,"text":"Looking at the five major rivers that feed Bangladesh."},{"time":589000,"text":"And now let's look from the south, looking up, and let's see this in relief."},{"time":595000,"text":"A minimum of 20 to 40 inches of increase in seas,"},{"time":601000,"text":"coupled with increasing flows from the Himalayas. And take a look at this."},{"time":610000,"text":"As many as 100 million refugees from Bangladesh could be expected to migrate"},{"time":619000,"text":"into India and into China."},{"time":623000,"text":"This is the difficulty that one country faces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628000,"text":"But if you look at the globe, all around the earth, wherever there is low-lying area,"},{"time":636000,"text":"populated areas near the water,"},{"time":639000,"text":"you will find increase in sea level that will challenge our way of life."},{"time":643000,"text":"Sub-Saharan Africa, and even our own San Francisco Bay Area."},{"time":650000,"text":"We're all in this together."},{"time":653000,"text":"This is not something that happens far away to people that we don't know."},{"time":657000,"text":"Global warming is something that happens to all of us, all at once."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663000,"text":"As are these newly emerging communicable diseases,"},{"time":667000,"text":"names that you hadn't heard 20 years ago: ebola, lhasa fever, monkey pox."},{"time":672000,"text":"With the erosion of the green belt separating animals from humans,"},{"time":677000,"text":"we live in each other's viral environment."},{"time":680000,"text":"Do you remember, 20 years ago, no one had ever heard of West Nile fever?"},{"time":684000,"text":"And then we watched, as one case arrived on the East Coast of the United States"},{"time":688000,"text":"and it marched every year, westwardly."},{"time":692000,"text":"Do you remember no one had heard of ebola"},{"time":695000,"text":"until we heard of hundreds of people dying in Central Africa from it?"},{"time":699000,"text":"It's just the beginning, unfortunately."},{"time":701000,"text":"There have been 30 novel emerging communicable diseases"},{"time":708000,"text":"that begin in animals that have jumped species in the last 30 years."},{"time":715000,"text":"It's more than enough reason for pessimism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718000,"text":"But now let's look at the case for optimism. (Laughter)"},{"time":723000,"text":"Enough of the bad news. Human beings have always risen to the challenge."},{"time":728000,"text":"You just need to look at the list of Nobel laureates to remind ourselves."},{"time":734000,"text":"We've been here before, paralyzed by fear, paralyzed into inaction,"},{"time":740000,"text":"when some -- probably one of you in this room -- jumped into the breach"},{"time":746000,"text":"and created an organization like Physicians for Social Responsibility,"},{"time":751000,"text":"which fought against the nuclear threat,"},{"time":754000,"text":"Medicins Sans Frontieres, that renewed our commitment to disaster relief,"},{"time":760000,"text":"Mohamed ElBaradei, and the tremendous hope and optimism that he"},{"time":764000,"text":"brought all of us, and our own Muhammad Yunus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":768000,"text":"We've seen the eradication of smallpox."},{"time":772000,"text":"We may see the eradication of polio this year."},{"time":775000,"text":"Last year, there were only 2,000 cases in the world."},{"time":779000,"text":"We may see the eradication of guinea worm next year --"},{"time":783000,"text":"there are only 35,000 cases left in the world."},{"time":785000,"text":"20 years ago, there were three and a half million."},{"time":789000,"text":"And we've seen a new disease, not like the 30 novel emerging communicable diseases."},{"time":796000,"text":"This disease is called sudden wealth syndrome. (Laughter)"},{"time":802000,"text":"It's an amazing phenomenon."},{"time":805000,"text":"All throughout the technology world, we're seeing young people bitten by this"},{"time":809000,"text":"disease of sudden wealth syndrome."},{"time":813000,"text":"But they're using their wealth in a way that their forefathers never did."},{"time":819000,"text":"They're not waiting until they die to create foundations."},{"time":823000,"text":"They're actively guiding their money, their resources, their hearts, their commitments,"},{"time":828000,"text":"to make the world a better place."},{"time":830000,"text":"Certainly, nothing can give you more optimism than that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":833000,"text":"More reasons to be optimistic:"},{"time":836000,"text":"in the '60s, and I am a creature of the '60s, there was a movement."},{"time":841000,"text":"We all felt that we were part of it, that a better world was right around the corner,"},{"time":845000,"text":"that we were watching the birth of a world free of hatred and violence and prejudice."},{"time":851000,"text":"Today, there's another kind of movement. It's a movement to save the earth."},{"time":856000,"text":"It's just beginning."},{"time":858000,"text":"Five weeks ago, a group of activists from the business community gathered together"},{"time":865000,"text":"to stop a Texas utility from building nine coal-fired electrical plants"},{"time":871000,"text":"that would have contributed to destroying the environment."},{"time":876000,"text":"Six months ago, a group of business activists gathered together to join with the"},{"time":882000,"text":"Republican governor in California to pass AB 32,"},{"time":886000,"text":"the most far-reaching legislation in environmental history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891000,"text":"Al Gore made presentations in the House and the Senate as an expert witness."},{"time":900000,"text":"Can you imagine? (Laughter)"},{"time":903000,"text":"We're seeing an entente cordiale between science and religion that five years ago"},{"time":909000,"text":"I would not have believed, as the evangelical community"},{"time":913000,"text":"has understood the desperate situation of global warming."},{"time":919000,"text":"And now 4,000 churches have joined the environmental movement."},{"time":924000,"text":"It is something to be greatly optimistic about."},{"time":928000,"text":"The European 20-20-20 plan is an amazing breakthrough,"},{"time":934000,"text":"something that should make all of us feel that hope is on the horizon."},{"time":939000,"text":"And on April 14th, there will be Step Up Day, where there will be a thousand"},{"time":944000,"text":"individual mobilized social activist movements in the United States on protest"},{"time":951000,"text":"against legislation -- pushing for legislation to stop global warming."},{"time":957000,"text":"And on July 7th, around the world, I learned only yesterday,"},{"time":961000,"text":"there will be global Live Earth concerts."},{"time":965000,"text":"And you can feel this optimistic move to save the earth in the air."}]},{"cues":[{"time":971000,"text":"Now, that doesn't mean that people understand that global warming"},{"time":975000,"text":"hurts the poorest and the weakest the most."},{"time":979000,"text":"That means that people are beginning the first step,"},{"time":981000,"text":"which is acting out of their own self-interest."},{"time":984000,"text":"But I am seeing in the major funders, in CARE, Rockefeller,"},{"time":988000,"text":"Rockefeller Brothers Fund, Hewlett, Mercy Corps, you guys, Google,"},{"time":993000,"text":"so many other organizations, a beginning of understanding that we need"},{"time":998000,"text":"to work not just on primary prevention of global warming,"},{"time":1001000,"text":"but on the secondary prevention of the consequences of global warming"},{"time":1006000,"text":"on the poorest and the most vulnerable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1011000,"text":"But for me, I have another reason to be an incurable optimist."},{"time":1016000,"text":"And you've heard so many inspiring stories here, and I heard so many last night"},{"time":1022000,"text":"that I thought I would share a little bit of mine."},{"time":1025000,"text":"My background is not exactly conventional medical training."},{"time":1029000,"text":"And I lived in a Himalayan monastery, and I studied with a very wise teacher,"},{"time":1034000,"text":"who kicked me out of the monastery one day and told me that it was my destiny --"},{"time":1039000,"text":"it felt like Yoda -- it is your destiny to go to work for WHO"},{"time":1045000,"text":"and to help eradicate smallpox,"},{"time":1047000,"text":"at a time when there was no smallpox program."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1051000,"text":"It should make you optimistic that smallpox no longer exists"},{"time":1055000,"text":"because it was the worst disease in history."},{"time":1059000,"text":"In the last century -- that's the one that was seven years ago --"},{"time":1065000,"text":"half a billion people died from smallpox:"},{"time":1067000,"text":"more than all the wars in history,"},{"time":1070000,"text":"more than any other infectious disease in the history of the world."},{"time":1075000,"text":"In the Summer of Love, in 1967, two million people, children, died of smallpox."},{"time":1082000,"text":"It's not ancient history."},{"time":1085000,"text":"When you read the biblical plague of boils, that was smallpox."},{"time":1090000,"text":"Pharaoh Ramses the Fifth, whose picture is here, died of smallpox."},{"time":1097000,"text":"To eradicate smallpox, we had to gather the largest United Nations army in history."},{"time":1103000,"text":"We visited every house in India, searching for smallpox -- 120 million houses,"},{"time":1109000,"text":"once every month, for nearly two years."},{"time":1113000,"text":"In a cruel reversal, after we had almost conquered smallpox --"},{"time":1116000,"text":"and this is what you must learn as a social entrepreneur, the realm of the final inch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1122000,"text":"When we had almost eradicated smallpox, it came back again,"},{"time":1126000,"text":"because the company town of Tatanagar drew laborers,"},{"time":1131000,"text":"who could come there and get employment."},{"time":1134000,"text":"And they caught smallpox in the one remaining place that had smallpox,"},{"time":1138000,"text":"and they went home to die."},{"time":1140000,"text":"And when they did, they took smallpox to 10 other countries"},{"time":1144000,"text":"and reignited the epidemic."},{"time":1146000,"text":"And we had to start all over again."},{"time":1150000,"text":"But, in the end, we succeeded, and the last case of smallpox:"},{"time":1157000,"text":"this little girl, Rahima Banu -- Barisal, in Bangladesh --"},{"time":1164000,"text":"when she coughed or breathed, and the last virus of smallpox left her lungs"},{"time":1171000,"text":"and fell on the dirt and the sun killed that last virus,"},{"time":1177000,"text":"thus ended a chain of transmission of history's greatest horror."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1185000,"text":"How can that not make you optimistic?"},{"time":1191000,"text":"A disease which killed hundreds of thousands in India, and blinded half of"},{"time":1197000,"text":"all of those who were made blind in India, ended."},{"time":1202000,"text":"And most importantly for us here in this room, a bond was created."},{"time":1209000,"text":"Doctors, health workers, from 30 different countries,"},{"time":1212000,"text":"of every race, every religion, every color, worked together,"},{"time":1217000,"text":"fought alongside each other,"},{"time":1220000,"text":"fought against a common enemy, didn't fight against each other."},{"time":1225000,"text":"How can that not make you feel optimistic for the future?"},{"time":1230000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":1232000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}